nTwo Israeli soldiers were wounded in a\nclash with Egyptian forces near Kissufim in the Gaza strip. This\nfollows another clash on 23 August in the same area. (Press)\n\nThe American air attaché in Cairo reports\nthat 19 IL-28 Soviet light bombers, purchased by Egypt from the\nSoviet bloc, were observed at Luxor airport, about 350 miles\nsouth of Cairo. The attaché states that the bombers were prob-\nably moved from Cairo West airport.\n\nThe American embassy in Amman reports\nthat previous Jordanian claims regarding Israeli mobilization\nand preparations for war have been partly based on reports ac-\nquired by a new intelligence net set up after the ouster of General\nGlubb. The net is headed by inexperienced officers who, under\npressure to supply information, are in contact with a very large\nnumber of new sources, many unreliable and discredited by older\nintelligence networks. The embassy comments that one result\nof this will probably be continued alarmist reports from Jordan\nregarding Israeli preparations for war.\n\nAccording to the American air attaché in\nBaghdad, Iraq is trying to obtain 10 Mark VI Hunter fighter air-\ncraft for its air force. Iraq has also selected 10 jet-trained pi-\nlots to go to the United Kingdom for several months' training on\nthe Hunters. Iraq now has 23 jet fighters", "token_count": 225, "token_end_0based": 224, "token_start_0based": 0, "token_text": "the arab-israeli situation information as of 1700 24 august two israeli soldiers were wounded in a clash with egyptian forces near kissufim in the gaza strip this follows another clash on 23 august in the same area press the american air attach in cairo reports that 19 il-28 soviet light bombers purchased by egypt from the soviet bloc were observed at luxor airport about 350 miles south of cairo the attach states that the bombers were prob ably moved from cairo west airport the american embassy in amman reports that previous jordanian claims regarding israeli mobilization and preparations for war have been partly based on reports ac quired by a new intelligence net set up after the ouster of general glubb the net is headed by inexperienced officers who under pressure to supply information are in contact with a very large number of new sources many unreliable and discredited by older intelligence networks the embassy comments that one result of this will probably be continued alarmist reports from jordan regarding israeli preparations for war according to the american air attach in baghdad iraq is trying to obtain 10 mark vi hunter fighter air craft for its air force iraq has also selected 10 jet-trained pi lots to go to the united kingdom for several months training on the hunters iraq now has 23 jet fighters", "unred_source_page": 8}
